What did I just read? How can people say this was a good series? The English is pretty broken, and unless I missed something, they didn't explain anything about Kei's backstory or about her scar. I thought they were joking when Kei brought up breaking up because Hiroki goes full doomer and accepts the breakup and she kicks him and said I hate that side of you(which I thought implied she was joking and hated how he took it serious and became so depressed). Overall, shit characters, shit relationships, shit translation. 3/10

@High_As_Icarus I guess its kind of weird. The idea of hentais and doujins having a remote amount of plot or story is unusual, maybe even unsettling. I mean, why shouldn't it be? They're simply material for us to read and get our rocks off. But then there comes works like these, with material that can be as read into as more contemporary material. And I agree that the scars are a bit... attractive. Just glad to see another person read deep into these questionable frontiers.

It is genuinely difficult to put my feelings into words. I feel them breaking up was for the best. I think the dude needed to mature and grow up a bit, and the chick needed to figure out what she actually wanted. I wish we got to see more of her not only cuz the art is glorious, but I find body markings really interesting. It's something really small that gives such a great impression on the reader.
